The paper deals with a geometric packing problem involving axis-aligned rectangles, which falls under computational geometry (cs.CG). The use of a knapsack and profit values suggests a connection to algorithms and data structures (cs.DS) and discrete mathematics (cs.DM). The development of a PTAS and approximation algorithms suggests a connection to approximation algorithms and heuristics (cs.GT) and complexity theory (cs.CC).
